critter.name: Stringfish
critter.desc: The stringfish grows slowly, but also lives quite a long time for a fish, with up to 15 years being typical. Consequently, while it takes a while, they can get quite large-perhaps even up to six feet long! The stringfish is perhaps the best embodiment in the fish world of 'slow and steady wins the race.'
critter.quote: OH MY GOSH! I caught a stringfish! Five more and I'll have a guitarfish!
